      • parseFolder

        public void parseFolder(java.lang.String path,
               boolean recursive,
               java.lang.String extension)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        java.text.ParseException
        Search folder (when recursive is true - and subfolders) for files with specific extension (or all files when extension if null) and parses them
        Parameters:
        path - path of the folder to walk through - must not be null
        recursive - should be walkthrough recursive?
        extension - extension of files to parse, or null to parse all files
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException - when problem with parsing
        java.io.IOException - problem with reading the file
